Responsive Websites -
•Landscape Screen  - width greater than height(laptop).
•Portrait Screen - height greater than width(Mobile).

Units & ViewPorts

Absolute units
1.Pixels : (DPR) Fixed Size

Relative
1.Percentage: Take size according to their parent
2.em: Relative to the font size of the parent
3.rem: Rlative to the root element font size

ViewPort Units
vw: According ViewPort width
vh: According ViewPort height
vmin,vmax:ViewPort Maximum(If ViewPort height is max and ViewPort width)

Modern Units
ch: width of the "0" chararcter in the current font. Useful for input fields
lh:Relative to the line height of the elmemnt

------------------------LAYOUTS-----------------
1.FlexBox
•Bydefault flex-direction  - row, cross axis - y-axis and main axis - x-axis
•alignItems - works in cross-axis
•Justify Content - works in main-axis
•flex-Direction - coloum then(main-axis - y-axis and cross axis - x-axis)
©flex-wrap - wrap (wrap up - containg element without shrinking child element)
•flex-shrink - 0 (its for child)
•give gap - to the parent 

2.Grid Layout
•give display grid to the parent
•grid-template-columns: columns width (can be two or four) , (1fr,1fr,1fr,1fr)
•grid-teplate-rows: same as columns
align-self and justify-self

if you are working with small element work with - flexbox
and if you are working with like dashboard - work with grid

----------------media queris-----------------------
